Package bacnet.datamodel.proteomics

Class NTermCreateData

  • java.lang.Object
    • bacnet.datamodel.proteomics.NTermCreateData
  • public class NTermCreateData
extends java.lang.Object
    Transform excel table describing all N-Terminal peptides found in Listeria
  • Find the position of each peptide in Listeria genome
  • create a NGS data from it
Author:
christophebecavin

      private void initializeGenomeSequence​(Genome genome)
      Get all 6 possible amino acids sequence of the genome

      Initialize:
      genomeAA - In frame sequence genomeAACompl - In frame sequence complementary genomeAAMinus - Minus -1 bp sequence genomeAAMinusCompl - Minus -1 bp sequence complementary genomeAAPlus - Plus 1 bp sequence genomeAAPlusCompl - Plus 1 bp sequence complementary

      Can save these genomes in NTermUtils.getPATH()+"Genome aminoacid mapping/"
      private void mapPeptide()
      On each of the 6 frame genome, map the different peptide
      private java.util.ArrayList<Sequence> mapSequence​(java.lang.String sequence)
      Map an amino acide sequence to 6 frame Genomes
      From initializeGenomeSequence() we get all 6 possible amino acids sequence of the genome, and map the peptide
      The different mapping coordinates are transformed into nucleotide coordinates (= genome coordinates)
      void modifyPathArray()
      Check PATHARRAY and had columns if needed

      Two types of array are possible: one with only one experiment (contains only one column with "# spectra") one with only multiple experiments (contains many columns containing "# spectra")

      For The first type:
      Check if PATHARRAY table is complete = has 8 columns, first column is the list of peptide, soluble and insoluble contains "TRUE" and "FALSE" and no "yes"
      Change "TRUE" and "FALSE" to "yes" and "no" Remove line with NH2-free peptide

      For the second type:

      • initializeGenomeSequence

        private void initializeGenomeSequence​(Genome genome)
        Get all 6 possible amino acids sequence of the genome

        Initialize:
      • genomeAA - In frame sequence
      • genomeAACompl - In frame sequence complementary
      • genomeAAMinus - Minus -1 bp sequence
      • genomeAAMinusCompl - Minus -1 bp sequence complementary
      • genomeAAPlus - Plus 1 bp sequence
      • genomeAAPlusCompl - Plus 1 bp sequence complementary

        Can save these genomes in NTermUtils.getPATH()+"Genome aminoacid mapping/"
Parameters:
genome - to read

  • modifyPathArray

    public void modifyPathArray()
    Check PATHARRAY and had columns if needed

    Two types of array are possible:
  • one with only one experiment (contains only one column with "# spectra")
  • one with only multiple experiments (contains many columns containing "# spectra")

    For The first type:
    Check if PATHARRAY table is complete = has 8 columns, first column is the list of peptide, soluble and insoluble contains "TRUE" and "FALSE" and no "yes"
  • Change "TRUE" and "FALSE" to "yes" and "no"
  • Remove line with NH2-free peptide

    For the second type:
